        "id": 2165445,
        "name": "Oliver V",
        "username": "Oliver_V",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/oliver_v/{size}/2788_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-16T03:42:24.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is one of those weird wines I\u2019ve had forever and can\u2019t remember where I acquired it. Was hoping to open it at Xmas, but had a terrible cold so decided I was too mean to share it. Glad I waited.</p>\n<p>From magnum, PnP. Cork was a disaster but the wine was looking pretty youthful in color.</p>\n<p>Powerful nose of black cherry, soil and burnt ash. Burly but with a floral undertone; Mike Tyson carrying a bunch of tulips. Fabulously balanced. Tart but not excessively so, and impressively concentrated. Significant tannin, but the wine is big enough to wear it.</p>\n<p>Has the guts to age a while longer (probably- I am not very experienced with Burgundy), but I can\u2019t imagine a more perfect time to drink this.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T22:42:08.157Z",
